    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, can you help me understand the difference between a \"confidentiality period\" and a \"survival clause\" in a standard contract? I'm trying to make sure I don't miss anything important.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A confidentiality period and a survival clause are two distinct provisions in a contract. A confidentiality period typically restricts an individual or organization from using sensitive information once a contract has been terminated or expired. A survival clause, on the other hand, ensures that certain terms or provisions in the contract remain in effect even after the contract itself has ended or terminated. This helps maintain continuity and prevents ambiguity.",
      "source": "target",
